  "description": "Non-Ciel, on-disk open PDK (open-ecos icsprout55). Enriched beyond tech-LEF: std-cell LEF/CDL/Verilog for three Vt flavors (RVT/HVT/LVT, the H7C library) plus the IO library (LEF + Liberty across tt/ss/ff corners) are now presented, so the PDK is PLACE-ABLE (LEF-driven P&R). corners[] declares the three core PVT corners (V1.08/1.20/1.32) the std cells are characterized at (per the H7C TYPICAL_V1P2_T25 datasheet). NOT YET PRESENTED (gates full sign-off): std-cell timing .lib and .gds are download-on-demand via `make unzip` (large files, not in the git mirror) \u2014 added to cell_libraries[].lib once materialized on the install root; and SPICE/RC models + DRC/LVS decks are not yet released upstream, so STA-corner timing, extraction, and DRC/LVS remain gated. The descriptor describes WHAT EXISTS; a resolver errors only when a flow needs collateral not yet presented. Mirrored under github.com/vyges-tools."
